  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you post blogs on Quora?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Quora has transitioned away from its blog feature that previously allowed users to create and share blog posts. Instead, Quora now focuses on its main Q&A format. However, you can still share long-form content on Quora by following these steps:\n\n1. **Create a Quora Account**: If you don't already have an account, sign up for one at [Quora](https://www.quora.com/).\n\n2. **Navigate to the Main Feed**: Once you are logged in, you'll be on the main feed page.\n\n3. **Start a Post**:\n   - Click on the \u201cAdd Question or Post\u201d button at the top right of the page.\n   - Select the \u201cPost\u201d option.\n\n4. **Write Your Content**:\n   - Enter your title in the \"What's your post about?\" field.\n   - Write your content in the main body area. Quora supports rich text formatting, so you can add headings, links, images, and other formatting elements to your post.\n\n5. **Add Relevant Topics**:\n   - Below the post, you can add relevant topics to ensure your content reaches the right audience. Type in a few keywords related to your post and select the most appropriate topics.\n\n6. **Review and Publish**:\n   - Double-check your content for any errors or omissions.\n   - Once you're satisfied, click the \u201cPost\u201d button to publish your content.\n\n7. **Engage with the Community**:\n   - After publishing, engage with users who comment on your post or ask questions related to your content. This will help increase visibility and interaction.\n\nRemember, Quora is primarily a platform for sharing knowledge through questions and answers, so framing your long-form content in a way that invites engagement and discussion can be particularly effective.",
